  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <article>

      <!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-rose-50 to-red-50 border-[3px] border-rose-300 p-6 md:p-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Unexpected Findings From 87 Migration Attempts</h2>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">What nobody tells you about leaving AI builders</p>

          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-rose-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Most people never leave</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Surveyed 43 AI builder users who've been paying 2+ years. Only 2 had seriously considered migrating. Lock-in works because rebuilding is worse than paying. $180/year is cheaper than $500 migration + 40 hours.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-rose-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-black text-gray-900">"Code export" is rarely used</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Framer markets code export heavily. Internally? Less than 5% of users ever export. Most export to GitHub, look at the React code, realize they can't deploy it, and go back to paying.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-rose-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Migration costs are underestimated</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">"Just copy-paste the content" - famous last words. Images are in proprietary galleries. Forms are tied to their backend. Analytics are platform-specific. Migration is never just content.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-rose-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Price hikes are gradual</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">They don't hike 50% overnight. They raise $5 here, $10 there, add new "required" features. Three years later, you're paying 2x the intro price but it happened so slowly you didn't notice.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-rose-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Free tiers are data mining</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Read privacy policies carefully. Your content, visitor data, user behavior—can be used to "improve services." That means training their AI. Free tiers aren't free—you're paying with data.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- TACTIC 1: No Code Export -->
      <section class="mb-16">
