          <h3 class="font-black text-red-900 mb-3">The Tactic</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Make it technically impossible to leave. No code export button. No download option. Your site lives on their servers, and if you stop paying, it disappears within days.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong>Who does this:</strong> Wix, Squarespace, Durable, Mixo, Webflow (technically has export but limited), 10Web (WordPress export isn't portable).
          </p>

          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong>The reality:</strong> This isn't a technical limitation. It's a business decision. CodeDesign.ai proves clean code export is possible. Others choose not to implement it because lock-in = recurring revenue.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-gray-100 border-l-[4px] border-gray-400 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-800">
              <strong>Personal experience:</strong> I've watched friends spend $2,000+ building sites on Wix, then try to leave 3 years later. They can't export. Either keep paying $30/month forever or rebuild from scratch. That's the trap.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- TACTIC 2: Proprietary Formats -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-[#F5521A] text-white font-black text-xl flex items-center justify-center">2</div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900">The "Export Is Useless" Trick</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-[3px] border-yellow-300 p-6 mb-6">
          <h3 class="font-black text-yellow-900 mb-3">The Tactic</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Technically offer export, but make it useless. Wix offers "XML export" that no other tool can read. Framer exports React code that requires build tools and React knowledge. It's export in name only.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong>Who does this:</strong> Framer (React export, not HTML), Wix (XML export, useless), Webflow (HTML/CSS export but missing CMS functionality).
          </p>

          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong>The psychological game:</strong> They can honestly say "we offer export" in marketing. But when users try to actually use it, they hit a wall of technical complexity. Most give up and keep paying.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-yellow-100 border-l-[4px] border-yellow-600 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-yellow-900">
              <strong>The frustration loop:</strong> You export from Framer, get a React project, spend 20 hours trying to deploy it, realize you need React expertise you don't have, go back to paying $15/month. The "export" feature exists to shut up complaints, not to actually help you leave.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- TACTIC 3: Price Hikes -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-[#F5521A] text-white font-black text-xl flex items-center justify-center">3</div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900">The "Annual Price Hike" Strategy</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-orange-50 border-[3px] border-orange-300 p-6 mb-6">
          <h3 class="font-black text-orange-900 mb-3">The Tactic</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Offer a low introductory price for year 1. Raise prices 10-30% in year 2. You're locked in with your site built, so you pay. This is especially common with Wix and Squarespace.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong>Real examples from my testing:</strong>
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li>Wix: $16/mo intro → $27/mo renewal (+69%)</li>
            <li>Squarespace: $23/mo intro → $30/mo renewal (+30%)</li>
            <li>Webflow: $23/mo intro → $31/mo renewal (+35%)</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="bg-orange-100 border-l-[4px] border-orange-600 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-orange-900">
              <strong>The lock-in mechanism:</strong> By the time the price hike hits, you've invested months building your site. Migrating costs $500+ in developer fees or 40+ hours of work. Most people just pay the higher price. That's the calculation they're banking on.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- TACTIC 4: The "Free" Funnel -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-[#F5521A] text-white font-black text-xl flex items-center justify-center">4</div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900">The "Free Trial" Bait</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-purple-50 border-[3px] border-purple-300 p-6 mb-6">
