            <li><strong>Wix:</strong> Huge ads, no custom domain, 500MB storage</li>
            <li><strong>Durable:</strong> Expires in 30 days, site goes offline</li>
            <li><strong>Framer:</strong> Best free plan, but still has Framer branding and no custom domain</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong>The psychological trap:</strong> You invest time building on the free plan. Once you've invested 10+ hours, abandoning that work feels worse than paying $15/month. They know this.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-purple-100 border-l-[4px] border-purple-600 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-purple-900">
              <strong>The sunk cost fallacy:</strong> "I've already spent 20 hours building this on Wix free plan. I can't just abandon that work." That's exactly what they're counting on. The free plan isn't free—it costs you time, and that time creates lock-in.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- TACTIC 5: Integration Lock-In -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-[#F5521A] text-white font-black text-xl flex items-center justify-center">5</div>
