            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              <strong class="text-rose-600">Price hikes are a lock-in tactic.</strong> They offer low introductory prices ($16-23/month) to get you started building. Once you've invested months creating content, they raise prices 30-69% for year 2. Real examples: Wix $16→$27 (+69%), Squarespace $23→$30 (+30%), Webflow $23→$31 (+35%). The calculation: you've invested 50+ hours building. Migrating costs $500+ in developer fees or 40+ hours of work. Most people just pay the higher price. They hike gradually ($5 here, $10 there) so you don't notice. Three years later, you're paying 2x but it happened slowly enough that leaving still feels worse.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-rose-50 to-red-50 rounded-xl p-6 border-2 border-rose-100">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Are free AI website builders really free?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
